<chapter id="installation">
<title>Installation</title>

<para>
In this chapter are detailed installation notes written.
</para>

<sect1 id="installation.getting-started">
<title id="installation.getting-started.title">Getting started</title>
<para>

&name; enables PHP scripters to quickly create a form for use with a MySQL
database table. The resulting form can be used to Add, Change, Copy, or Delete
records.

</para>
<para>

&name; is available for download from <ulink
url="http://phpmyedit.sourceforge.net">Sourceforge.net</ulink>. Extract, or unzip,
the program files to your computer's hard disk. The download file includes icons
and various language files which belong in sub-folders.

</para>
<important><para>

Before installing the files on your webserver, the filenames are
case sensitive (don't force lower case upon uploading). 

</para></important>
<para>

Point your web browser to the file named <filename>phpMyEditSetup.php</filename>
and log on to your MySQL database. The logon screen should resemble the picture
below.

</para>
<para>

<mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="images/logon.gif" format="gif"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>&name; logon screen</phrase></textobject>
<!-- <caption><para>TODO</para></caption> -->
</mediaobject>

</para>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="installation.table-selection">
<title id="installation.table-selection.title">Table selection</title>
<para>

After successfully logging on to your database server, a list of tables should
appear. Select a table and click Submit.

</para>
<para>

<mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="images/table-selection.gif" format="gif"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>&name; table selection screen</phrase></textobject>
<!-- <caption><para>TODO</para></caption> -->
</mediaobject>

</para>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="installation.id-selection">
<title id="installation.id-selection.title">ID selection</title>
<para>

After selecting a MySQL table a list of columns, or fields, should appear.
Select a unique numeric identifier and click Submit.

</para>
<para>

<mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="images/id-selection.gif" format="gif"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>&name; ID selection screen</phrase></textobject>
<!-- <caption><para>TODO</para></caption> -->
</mediaobject>

</para>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="installation.result-script">
<title id="installation.result-script.title">Result script</title>
<para>

After selecting a unique identifier, the script should appear in your web
browser. Highlight and copy the script, then paste it in your text editor.
Depending on your system configuration, the script may be written to the current
directory.

</para>
<para>

<mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="images/result-script.gif" format="gif"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>&name; result script screen</phrase></textobject>
<!-- <caption><para>TODO</para></caption> -->
</mediaobject>

</para>
</sect1>

